In this task we ask you to implement method throwing and catching
exceptions. In Java, Exceptions are handled using `try` and `catch`
statement like the example below

``` java
try{
    String s = methodThatCanThrowException();
}catch(ExceptionCaught e){
    //Do something
}

//Continue
```

When a method can throw an exception, it has to be specified in the
signature like the example below:

``` java
public static double divide(int i1, int i2) throws ArithmeticException
```

It means that it is possible that the method uses a statement like this:

``` java
throw new ArithmeticException();
```

Download [Divider](/course/LEPL1402/LearnException/Divider.java) and
read the comment to know what you have to do. Download [intellij
project](/course/LEPL1402/LearnException/LEPL1402_LearnException.zip)
with tests.

